pageContext.claim: “[Farmers have] been shut out, to a large extent, in China while they do business with China, they're still shut out.”
pageContext.analysis: China has put retaliatory tariffs on a number of agricultural products including soybeans and U.S. farmers are feeling the effects. Before the trade war between the two countries escalated, in 2017, China ranked second among countries importing U.S. agricultural goods.
